    "result": {"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"block":"project-euler-problems-201-to-300","title":"Problem 228: Minkowski Sums","description":"<section id=\"description\">\n<p>Let $S_n$ be the regular $n$-sided polygon – or shape – whose vertices $v_k (k = 1, 2, \\ldots, n)$ have coordinates:</p>\n<p>$$\\begin{align}\n&#x26; x_k = cos(\\frac{2k - 1}{n} × 180°) \\\\\n&#x26; y_k = sin(\\frac{2k - 1}{n} × 180°)\n\\end{align}$$</p>\n<p>Each $S_n$ is to be interpreted as a filled shape consisting of all points on the perimeter and in the interior.</p>\n<p>The Minkowski sum, $S + T$, of two shapes $S$ and $T$ is the result of adding every point in $S$ to every point in $T$, where point addition is performed coordinate-wise: $(u, v) + (x, y) = (u + x, v + y)$.</p>\n<p>For example, the sum of $S_3$ and $S_4$ is the six-sided shape shown in pink below:</p>\n<img class=\"img-responsive center-block\" alt=\"image showing S_3, S_4 and S_3 + S_4\" src=\"https://cdn.freecodecamp.org/curriculum/project-euler/minkowski-sums.png\" style=\"background-color: white; padding: 10px;\">\n<p>How many sides does $S_{1864} + S_{1865} + \\ldots + S_{1909}$ have?</p>\n</section>","id":"5900f4511000cf542c50ff63","hasEditableBoundaries":false,"instructions":null,"notes":null,"challengeType":1,"helpCategory":"Euler","videoUrl":null,"superBlock":"project-euler","translationPending":false,"forumTopicId":301871,"fields":{"blockName":"project-euler-problems-201-to-300","slug":"/learn/project-euler/project-euler-problems-201-to-300/problem-228-minkowski-sums","tests":[{"text":"<p><code>minkowskiSums()</code> should return <code>86226</code>.</p>","testString":"assert.strictEqual(minkowskiSums(), 86226);"}]},"required":[],"usesMultifileEditor":false,"challengeFiles":[{"fileKey":"scriptjs","ext":"js","name":"script","contents":"function minkowskiSums() {\n\n  return true;\n}\n\nminkowskiSums();","head":"","tail":"","editableRegionBoundaries":[],"history":["script.js"]}]}}},"pageContext":{"challen